I haven't worked on NES related things lately, keeping myself busy with MSX stuff instead, so I can't help you with any code or possible fixes in Sega Li. What I can tell you is that Jaleco sample player emulation is not accurate at all, it's enough to get the games working. So, if you find a way to loop samples in an emulator, it's likely not the same if you ever try your program on a real cartridge (or on an accurate emulator 10 years from now).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=115">hap</a> — Wed Nov 12, 2008 3:05 am</p><hr />
